      <p class="nospace" style="text-align: center; padding-top: 20px;">Simply put, a blood type can be defined as a red blood cell that contains a specific surface antigen (surface marker). Differences in human blood are due to the presence or abscence of certain protein molecules called antigens and antibodies. The antigens are located on the surface of the red blood cells and the antibodies are in the blood plasma. </p>
